Algorithms and programs. Representations of algorithms, flow-charts. Branching algorithms. Loops. Sub-algorithms. Developing algorithms for given text-based problems. Program structure. Names. Variables. Operations. Expressions. Boolean expressions, comparisons. Conditional statements. Loop statements. Lists. Functions. User input. Reading from a file. Writing to a file. Simple user interface.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Student will acquire the basics of algorithmic thinking and get acquainted with some of the programming techniques.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student - is motivated to use computers and to develop necessary programs for further studies; - can demonstrate basic programming constructs (branching, loops, subprogram) as programming sections; - can develop algorithms for simple text-based problems.
